an be attributed to Luclin.  I cannot disagree that we were lacking in the past, but thanks to foci, AA, and new spells we have certainly found a place of our own.  I am not a parse freak, but will just speak from my current experence as a decently equipped lvl 65 wizard.  In a constant pull XP group in an outdoor zone (horse) where I have potg/9 and KEI/tranq I am no longer limited by mana regen in what I can do, but in aggro.  With a good Paladin tank I can chain nuke from shortly after his 1st stun until it dies and repeat.  About the time my mana hits 70ish my 2 harvest abilities are returning and, I'm back up to 90+ again.  Given that I am using only the new PoP draughts in XP situations for 2.7 cast of about 1050 damage with focus items, and factoring in crits and non casting for waiting on MA aggro/harvest/etc I would guess I get about 250-300DPS.  <br>
<br>
But again this is situational, horse, 15% magi mana save earring, 23% damage focus, SCM3, SCS3, MC3, PoP FamiliarAA, 2xHarvests, KEI, POTG, FT15, SCF5 make it possible.  Adjust the DPS down for lack of any of the above accordingly and you can get an idea what a well played wizard can do.<br>
<br>
I have no clue what a mage does DPS wise, but I know from the experience of a LD guild mage with uber POP pet turning on me that you all are pretty fierce with pets alone! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But I will say the one to be afraid of now are the Command of Druzzil chanters and druids with PoP charmed pets!  These things put everyone to shame <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But love them in my group! <p><CENTER><EMBED src="http://members.cox.net/niteravn/Torrath.swf"
